getAlertActionLog

public java.util.List<AlertActionLog> getAlertActionLog()
Gets the value of the alertActionLog property.

This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the alertActionLog property.

For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

    getAlertActionLog().add(newItem);

Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list AlertActionLog
